******
[2] Canada (Prince Edward Island)
Date: Tue 7 Oct 2014
Source: CBC News [edited]
http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/prince-edward-island/ev-d68-strain-of-enterovirus-diagnosed-on-p-e-i-1.2791626


The 1st case of the EV-D68 strain of enterovirus has been diagnosed on Prince Edward Island [P.E.I.]. Chief Public Health Officer Dr. Heather Morrison announced Tuesday [7 Oct 2014] the patient is a child under the age of 10, who was treated in hospital and has since fully recovered. The EV-D68 virus usually causes mild respiratory infections and cold-like illnesses. It can be spread through coughing and sneezing or by close contact with infected persons. Dr. Morrison said she was not surprised to see a diagnosis on the Island since enteroviruses circulate every year with cases across Canada.

The P.E.I. department of health and wellness said most people who become ill with EV-D68 will recover at home, but anyone experiencing difficulty breathing or shortness of breath should see a doctor. Only hospitalized cases in P.E.I. with respiratory illness are being tested for EV-068.

